IMF’s Strauss-Kahn Held Over Alleged Sexual Assault, New York Police Say

-- B y   K a r e n   F r e i f e l d
-- 
2011-05-15T01:14:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-15/imf-s-strauss-kahn-held-over-alleged-sexual-assault-new-york-police-say.html
Dominique Strauss-Kahn , managing
director of the  International Monetary Fund , was pulled from an
Air France flight in  New York  today and held for questioning
about an alleged sexual assault, a police spokesman said.  The IMF head was being questioned over an incident in a
Manhattan hotel, New York Police Department spokesman Brian
Sessa said.  Strauss-Kahn hasn’t been charged over the alleged assault,
police said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Dan Hart  at 
 dahart@bloomberg.net  